author: news@mpnews.net (Staff)
title: Freshman football team bests Fairfield
text:
Freshman football team bests Fairfield Oct 14, 2015 
By ANDY KRUTSINGER 
Mt. Pleasant News 
The Mt. Pleasant freshman football team had a dominant second half on Friday evening in a 28-6 win over Fairfield. The Panthers were up just by six points at halftime, but outscored the Trojans 14-0 in the final two quarters to seal the win. 
Avante Henley had a big day running the ball for the Panthers. Henley had two touchdown runs, one of 73 yards and one of 14 yards, and finished the game with 186 yards rushing. Levi Puig also had a nice day, with 35-yards rushing. 
Tanner Box added to the rushing stats with a one-yard touchdown run. Jacob Stukerjurgen had a big day receiving with two catches for 25 yards, and David Blancas went 4-4 in extra point kicks. 
Tucker Johnson led the defense with a 48-yard interception return for a touchdown. Other big playmakers on defense were Bryce Anderson, Chase Lamm, Clayton Loving, Hunter Faul and James DeMeyer. 
The Panthers, who moved to 5-2 overall and 3-1 against district foes, will travel to Washington next Friday for a district road game starting at 5 p.m.
